# Decision Log
# Entries are ordered newest-to-oldest. Most recent decision is at the top.
#
# Entry shape (use this for every decision worth recording):
#
# ## <date> — <session/short title>
#
# ### <the claim, question, or choice being decided>
# - <what was decided>
# - **Why:** <the reasoning — often a constraint, a past incident, or a tradeoff that was weighed>
# - **How to apply:** <when/where this decision should govern future choices; note if it's narrow to one case or a standing rule>
#
# Only log decisions that aren't obvious from reading the code/diff — e.g. "we
# chose X over Y because Z" or "we verified this claim and it was wrong, here's
# what's actually true." Don't log routine implementation choices that a diff
# already shows.
